etition on all insurer decisions. The book covers all facets of the modern insurance sector, guiding readers through its complexities with empirical facts, institutional details, and quantitative modeling.An up-to-date textbook for graduate students in economics, finance, and insuranceCovers a broad range of topics, including insurance pricing, contract design, reinsurance, portfolio choice, and risk managementProvides promising new directions for future researchCan be taught in courses on asset pricing, corporate finance, industrial organization, and public economicsAn invaluable resource for policymakers seeking an empirical and institutional account of today’s insurance sector  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Insurance / General.2bisacsh  aAsset management.  aCOVID-19 crisis.  aDerivatives.  aFinancial regulation.  aFinancial stability.  aGlobal financial crisis.  aLeverage.  aLife insurance.  aMarket power.  aMinimum return guarantee.  aReinsurance.  aRisk-based capital regulation.  aShadow insurance.  aSystemic risk.  aVariable annuities.1 aYogo, Motohiro, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2023 Englishz978311131907008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2023z9783111318134oZDB-23-DBV40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691245973?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691245973423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691245973/original  a978-3-11-131907-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Business a